The topics covered during the course: introducing yourself and the others; countries, nations, languages; numbers; ordinal numbers; address; asking and giving phone numbers; home; family; food and drink; everyday activities.
The course focuses on the following grammatical areas:
Regular and irregular verbs; conjugation of reflexive verbs; possessive pronouns;  verb gustar ; prepositions of place; prepositions of time; imperative; use of hay  and está; use of  ser and estar.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at systematic development of all four language skills (reading, writing, listening, speaking) through a wide variety of tasks: 1) reading and listening to texts; 2) doing lexical exercises; 3) practicing grammar; 4) doing pronunciation exercisesLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course the learners will be able to read and understand simple texts (both oral and written) in Spanish and use everyday vocabulary and grammar covered during the course. The learners will be able to talk and write about her/himself, her/his family, favourite activities and can cope with ordering a meal at a café/restaurant. The learners will be able  to understand and to compile simple oral and written texts.
